rust-proxmox-installer-types (0.1.1-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * answer: declare `arc_max`, `copies`, and `minfree` in the filesystem
    options api schema so PDM and the automated installer accept answer files
    that set these ZFS / LVM tuning properties instead of rejecting them with
    a `400 Bad Request`.

  * answer: expose the `email_validate` function so downstream consumers like
    the PDM UI that generate answer files can apply the same check as
    pve-installer itself, keeping address validation consistent across UIs.

  * answer: validate the disk count against the selected ZFS/Btrfs RAID level
    on save when the prepared answer pins explicit disks, so impossible setups
    like RAIDZ-1 with one disk are rejected up front instead of failing only
    at install time.

 -- Proxmox Support Team <support@proxmox.com>  Thu, 28 May 2026 14:56:34 +0200

rust-proxmox-installer-types (0.1.0-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * initial release of proxmox-installer-types, a crate carrying the data
    types and wire-format definitions shared between the Proxmox automated
    installer, its post-installation hook and consumers like Proxmox
    Datacenter Manager that serve answer files. Split out from the
    pve-installer source tree so the same types can be reused from other
    Proxmox products without pulling in the rest of the installer code.

  * exposes the answer-file format, the system-information payload sent to the
    answer endpoint and the post-install webhook payload, plus a regex and
    schema for Proxmox subscription keys for downstream API consumers.

  * the optional `api-types` cargo feature wires the types up with
    proxmox-schema and proxmox-api-macro for backend integration, while the
    `legacy` feature keeps old snake_case answer-file keys parseable so
    pve-installer ISOs predating the schema-stable kebab-case form keep
    working.

 -- Proxmox Support Team <support@proxmox.com>  Thu, 07 May 2026 01:27:33 +0200
